args:
Hanabusa vows to repay his debt to Mitsuhide,
while Daikokuten is determined to be a better
friend to Ebisu. Now motivated to confront both
Ebisu and their own failings, the two of them
join the prince's party in battle.
I can't believe Ebisu got away after\nall that work we did to catch him.
Dude, give it a rest already! Sheesh!\nSo then, what do we do now?
I don't know what we CAN do—all I know\nis that surrender is not an option.
Isn't it, though? I mean, this whole thing\nis turning into a SERIOUS pain.
No! Lady Amaterasu would be furious!
Eh, that's fine. I can handle a scolding.

Look, catching that fish was pretty exciting,
and we had a few laughs along the way.
Why not call that our New Year's party
and just move on with life?

This whole delivering-good-fortune stuff
is a real pain in the butt. I mean, do you
REALLY care that much about some
crusty old tradition?
It's time to cut ourselves a break!
That would certainly be a relief\nto my innards. However...
As much as your proposal appeals to me,\nI cannot allow myself to partake!
Even though I'm the one telling\nyou it's okay to give up?
Oh, it is a great relief to have your consent\nto withdraw. But I still can't do it.
I came to this land to perform the\ntraditional dance of our people!
I wish to use my dancing to spread both\nfortune and the majesty of Hinomoto's\nproud culture throughout the world!

Beyond that, I can't spend the rest of my
life as a sad man with a weak stomach.
When I accepted this task, I felt strong—
I felt like I could change.
That's why I came here despite the stress\nit caused—and I have yet to dance!
If I do not dance, I am but a shell.\nThere would be nothing left for me\nbut the cold embrace of the grave!
Hey, let's dial it back a notch, yeah?\nYa got plenty what to live for!

The Twelve Wyrmclans tradition of
delivering good fortune is not some
trivial errand to be abandoned at the
first sign of strife or issue.
Like Hanabusa's dance, the deliveries are\na tradition that stretches back to antiquity.
Safeguarding such traditions is the\nprimary duty of the Great Twelve.
Out of a sense of pity and overindulgence\ntowards Ebisu, I have been dragging my\nclaws when it comes to this task.
But if I am to be a friend to him,\nI must tell him the hardest of truths.
For the trouble he now causes makes\nhim unworthy of the Great Twelve!
If he wishes to know what it means to\nserve in this capacity, it is my duty\nto educate him as to such.
Sounds like you two have figured out\nexactly what it is you're fighting for.

I have. But there is yet a reason beyond
what I have stated: If I do not fight,
there is someone I could never look
in the eyes again.
No, Lady Mitsuhide. It is you.
You are the one who gave me this chance,\ndespite my flaws. And that is a debt I\nintend to repay, whatever the cost.
You're sure talking the talk now.\nBut let's see if you can walk it.
All right, you two. Now that you have\nyour reasons, go and win this thing!
Ah, Mitsuhide. I should have known\nthis was your plan all along.
Cease with this folly\nOr you will die on my blade\nWretched dragon cat
Give back all the stuff\nSo that I can take my nap\nYou big mean kitty
New Year's means presents\nI want lots of gifts this year\nOkay thanks bye-byeeeee
The New Year is nigh\nI vow to greet it with dance\nBut my stomach. Argh.
Oh hey, haiku! I wanna do one!\nWait a sec... Just let me... Hang on...
A new year dawning\nWith the eternal battle\nOf cat versus mouse
Now let's reclaim that good fortune.\nTo battle, one and all!
